ns?) Additional sections? (Shipping info, sizing charts, profit margin calculators?) Or if you have more CSV data or a complete product list, please share it and I'll import everything immediately! Let me know what's missing and I'll add it right away. 📊 Update this proceed to specify which are best garments for either embroidery or sublimation.Full color or the dtg flex with more vibrant colors make a column to indicate which method is best.So that the designs are sent to the correct product type Perfect! I'll add expert columns for print method recommendations to help route designs to the correct product types. Using Tool | Operating Sheets Perfect! ✅ Your complete Printify catalog is now fully loaded with expert print method guidance! 📊 What You're Seeing Now: Main Product Catalog (Rows 1-6) 15 columns of complete data including: ✅ Original product details (name, pricing, materials, colors) ✅ NEW: Best Print Method - DTG/DTF or Embroidery recommendations ✅ NEW: DTG Compatible - YES ratings with quality levels ✅ NEW: Embroidery Ready - Compatibility indicators ✅ NEW: Sublimation Ready - All marked NO (cotton products) ✅ NEW: Color Vibrancy - Quality ratings for each product ✅ NEW: Design Routing Notes - Detailed guidance on when to use each product Expert Guidance Sections: 🔷 Print Method Selection Guide (Rows 13-17) Complete breakdown of: DTG - For full-color, photographic designs on cotton DTF - Newer flexible method for all materials Embroidery - Premium logos and text Sublimation - Polyester-only (none of your products support this) 🔷 Quick Reference (Rows 19-24) Fast decision-making shortcuts: Vibrant full-color → Bella Canvas 3001 Logo/text embroidery → Gildan 5000 or Hoodie Vintage looks → Comfort Colors 1717 USA-made premium → Bella Canvas 3001U 🎯 How to Route Your Designs: Full-color vibrant artwork? → Bella Canvas 3001 (DTG) Company logos/text? → Gildan 5000 or Hoodie (Embroidery) Trendy vintage designs? → Comfort Colors 1717 (DTG) Need USA-made? → Bella