y and versatility. Let me analyze your current t-shirt lineup and recommend the best streamlined selection. 📊 Current T-Shirt Analysis: Your 4 T-Shirts: Bella Canvas 3001 - $9.04 premium, 126 colors, premium soft Bella Canvas 3001U - $14.00 premium, 7 colors, USA-made (same quality as 3001) Comfort Colors 1717 - $10.72 premium, 61 colors, vintage aesthetic Gildan 5000 - $7.26 premium, 15 colors, budget/embroidery focus Key Distinction Analysis: Major Distinctions: ✅ Bella Canvas 3001 - Premium soft feel, industry standard, 126 colors ✅ Comfort Colors 1717 - UNIQUE vintage garment-dyed aesthetic (completely different look/feel) ⚠️ Bella Canvas 3001U - Same as 3001 but USA-made (niche market) ⚠️ Gildan 5000 - Budget option but thicker fabric for embroidery Minor/Overlapping: Bella Canvas 3001 vs 3001U = Same quality, just USA manufacturing Gildan 5000 is cheaper but Bella Canvas works fine for embroidery too 🎯 My Recommendation: Keep 2-3 Core T-Shirts Option 1: Streamlined (2 T-Shirts) - RECOMMENDED Keep only the products with distinct purposes: Bella Canvas 3001 ($9.04) - Your workhorse ✅ DTG Flex for vibrant designs ✅ Embroidery capable ✅ 126 colors = maximum flexibility ✅ Premium soft fabric Comfort Colors 1717 ($10.72) - Your specialty ✅ Unique vintage/Instagram aesthetic ✅ Garment-dyed look (can't get this elsewhere) ✅ DTG Flex compatible ✅ 61 trendy colors Remove: ❌ Bella Canvas 3001U (unless you need \"Made in USA\" branding) ❌ Gildan 5000 (Bella Canvas does everything it does, but better) Option 2: Keep 3 T-Shirts (if USA-made matters) Bella Canvas 3001 - Premium standard Bella Canvas 3001U - USA-made premium (for customers who specifically want domestic) Comfort Colors 1717 - Vintage aesthetic Remove: Gildan 5000 ✅ Optimized Catalog Strategy: For DTG Flex + Embroidery with Premium Fabrics: T-Shirt: Bella Canvas 3001 (does BOTH excellently) Hoodie: Gildan 18500 (keep it - it's your only hoodie and works great for both) Why this works: Bella Canvas 3001 has premium 4.2oz cotton = excellent DTG Flex vibrancy Bella Canvas 3001 has tight weave = embroidery looks sharp 126 colors = customers can choose any color for any design Comfort Colors gives you a differentiated product for trendy/vintage market 🔄 Should I update your catalog to: Option A: Ultra-Streamlined (Recommended) Remove: Bella Canvas 3001U, Gildan 5000 Keep: Bella Canvas 3001, Comfort Colors 1717, Gildan Hoodie Result: 2 tees + 1 hoodie (all premium, all versatile) Option B: Keep USA-Made Option Remove: Gildan 5000 only Keep: Bella Canvas 3001, 3001U, Comfort Colors 1717, Gildan Hoodie Result: 3 tees + 1 hoodie Option C: Keep Current Selection No changes, maintain all 4 t-shirts Which option would you like me to implement? I'll update the spreadsheet to reflect your optimized selection! 🎯 You can go ahead and just keep them but rank it so rank based on the top premium that have the versatility of embroidery and d t g flex.And then whatever's left, just put at the bottom of the list Perfect! I'll reorganize your catalog by ranking products based on premium quality + DTG Flex & Embroidery versatility at the top, with specialized/niche products at the bottom. Using Tool | Operating Sheets Perfect! ✅ Your catalog is now optimized and ranked by versatility! 📊 New Product Ranking Structure: 🏆 TIER 1: Premium Versatile (DTG Flex + Embroidery) Row 2: Bella Canvas 3001 - $9.04 premium 👑 #1 WORKHORSE - Does everything excellently 126 colors, premium soft, DTG Flex excellent, embroidery ready Row 3: Comfort Colors 1717 - $10.72 premium 🎨 Unique vintage aesthetic - Can't get this elsewhere 61 colors, garment-dyed, DTG Flex excellent, Instagram favorite Row 4: Gildan 18500 Hoodie - $15.89 premium 🧥 Only hoodie option - Versatile for both methods 39 colors, embroidery preferred, DTG Flex good ⭐ TIER 2: Premium Specialty Row 5: Bella Canvas 3001U USA-Made - $14.00 premium 🇺🇸 Same quality as 3001, but USA manufacturing For customers who specifically need domestic production Row